We love good Pesto Rice and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

== Prep the Veggies ==

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways and chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Roast the Broccoli ==

Put the @tenderstem broccoli{150%g} on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Toast the Pine Nuts ==

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @pine nuts{25} and toast until golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove the pine nuts to a #small bowl{}.

== Cook the Pancetta and Veggies ==

Put the frying pan back on medium-high heat, add a drizzle of @oil{} and the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}, stir-fry until starting to brown, about ~{3%minutes}. Add the shallot, courgette and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry until the veggies have softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Add the Spinach and Rice ==

Add the @baby spinach{125%g} to the pan in handfuls and fry until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Break up the @steamed basmati rice{1%pack} in the pack, then add to the pan with the veggies and stir everything together.

== Finish with Pesto and Cheese ==

Add the @unsalted butter{30%g}, @green pesto{45%g} and three-quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} to the pan and stir through until the butter and cheese are melted. Remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

== Serve ==

Serve the pesto rice in #bowls{} with the tenderstem broccoli on top. Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and the pine nuts.